OOP concepts
    * Class - A class is a blueprint
            from which individual objects are created
            - Can contain data member/Fields, Constructors, methods
    * Object - Is an entity that has state and behaviour
    * Inheritance - An object acquires all the properties
                    of a parent/object extends
                    public class B IS-A extends class A
                    public class Subaru extends Car
    * Polymorphism - Is when a task is performed differently'
        -           - Overiding and overloading
    * Abstraction - Hiding internal details and only showing the
                    functionalities
    * Encapsulation - Binding or wrapping code and data together
                    in a single unit